title.narrative: UK humanitarian aid to meet urgent needs following the impact of Typhoon Haiyan, Philippines

description.narrative: This activity (UK humanitarian aid to meet urgent needs following the impact of Typhoon Haiyan, Philippines) is a component of UK humanitarian support for response to Typhoon Haiyan, Philippines reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £76,605,450. This component benefits Philippines, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services . , with the following implementing partners: Agency for Technical Cooperation and Development (ACTED), British Red Cross, CANADEM, CARE International UK, Christian Aid, Crown Agents Limited, Defence Fuels Group, Disasters Emergency Committee, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO), Handicap International (UK), HelpAge International, Information Management and Mine Action Programs, Inc., International Committee of the Red Cross, International Health Partners (UK) Ltd, International Labour Organization (ILO), International Organization for Migration (IOM), Internews Europe, Norwegian Refugee Council, Oxford Policy Management, Plan International UK, RedR, Save the Children UK, Solidarités international, UK - Ministry of Defence, UK-Med, United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA), United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA), World Food Programme (WFP), World Health Organization (WHO). The start date is 10-11-2013 and the end date is 30-09-2015.
